  "prompt": "I do masturbation twice in a day. Does masturbation affects men's sperm count or does it cause infertility?",
  "response": "Masturbation generally does not have a significant impact on sperm count or overall male fertility. It is a normal and healthy sexual activity. Frequent ejaculation, whether through masturbation or sexual intercourse, may temporarily decrease the volume of ejaculate and the number of sperm in each ejaculation because the body needs time to replenish the sperm count. However, this does not lead to long-term changes in fertility for most men.\n\nInfertility can be influenced by many factors, including lifestyle, health conditions, genetics, and environmental exposures. If you have concerns about your sperm count or fertility, it would be best to consult with a healthcare provider or a specialist in male reproductive health. They can provide individualized advice and conduct any necessary evaluations.",
